main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Unalakleet, Alaska from January 23 to January 26, 1951, involving orange lights that appeared intermittently.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes., Individuals initially thought the lights were flares observed on six different nights., There were two Alaskan native boys who reported seeing lights in the sky., The investigation suggested the possibility of the lights being reflections from the sun or related to nearby aircraft., No conclusive explanation was provided for the phenomenon.
